  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined in law as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Typically, it involves three stages: placement (introducing illegal funds into the financial system), layering (concealing the source of the money through complex transactions), and integration (making the money appear legitimate). Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most countries have laws criminalizing these activities.",
